imdb.plot outline: Chef Vincent is an American reality television series on- TV Network (to be announced). The series follows the life of Chef Vincent, with flair in the kitchen and a love for the fabulous night life. Chef Vincent takes up residence at the world famous Marlin Hotel 1200 Collins Ave, Miami Beach Florida, the mecca for great food, fantastic fashion and heart throbbing music. With his finesse and debonair French style, Chef Vincent attracts all kinds of beautiful women by the droves. Chef Vincent's celebrity friends stop by unexpectedly on a regular. At any given time you may end up dining right next to J-Lo, Rihanna, Brad Pitt or Will Smith to name a few. Each episode will guest star a celebrity guest from all genres. The Network has once again capitalized on its knack for finding and fostering top creative talent, while still delivering on the personalities and conflict that make for deliciously fun entertainment. Chefs Vincent also takes on unique culinary trials such as working with unusual and exotic foods and catering for a range of demanding celebrity personalities. His first celebrity guest comes from the ruff and rugged tarmac of the NFL, Running Back superstar Thomas Jones of The New York Jets. In this first episode, Thomas Jones will host a huge event for his newly formed company as he enlists the help of Chef Vincent to blend together extraordinary mouthwatering dishes. These two unlikely subjects will take you on a roller coaster ride of excitement as they find out together that people are the same all over
